{"title_page": "Maharaja Agrasen Institute of Technology", "text_new": "{{Use dmy dates|date=October 2018}}\n{{Use Indian English|date=October 2018}}\n{{Infobox university\n| name = Maharaja Agrasen Institute of Technology\n| image_name = Maharaja Agrasen Institute of Technology logo.PNG\n| caption = \n| established = 1999\n| type = [[Private school|Private]]\n| motto = Udyamena hi sidhyanti karyani na manorathaih ([[Sanskrit]])\n| mottoeng = Work gets accomplished by effort, not merely by wishing\n| director = Nand Kishore Garg <ref>https://www.mait.ac.in/index.php/institute/director-general-message</ref>\n| head_label = Neelam Sharma\t\n| city = [[New Delhi]]\n| country = [[India]]\n| faculty = \n| students = \n| coordinates = {{coord|28.722366|77.065980|region:IN-DL_type:edu|display=inline,title}}\n| campus = [[urban area|Urban]]\n| free_label = Nickname\n| free = MAIT\n| affiliations = [[Guru Gobind Singh Indraprastha University]]\n| colours = Red {{color box|#cc0000}}\n| website = {{url|http://www.mait.ac.in/}}\n}}\n\n'''Maharaja Agrasen Institute of Technology''' ('''MAIT''') is a private engineering college, located in [[Rohini, Delhi]], [[India]].  Established in 1999, the institute is approved by [[AICTE]] and affiliated to [[Guru Gobind Singh Indraprastha University]].<ref name=\":0\"/>\n\n== Departments ==\n\n; Sciences \n\n* Applied Sciences\n\n; Management \n\n* MBA\n\n== Admission ==\nAdmission to all courses is through common counseling of [[Guru Gobind Singh Indraprastha University]].\n\n==Campus==\n[[File:MAIT Administrative Block.JPG|thumb|Administrative Block]]\n[[File:MAIT Library.JPG|thumb|MAIT Library|alt=|180x180px]]MAIT\u2019s campus is composed of 10 blocks with a learning resource centre.<ref name=\":0\">{{Cite web|url=http://mait.ac.in/|title=Welcome to MAIT|website=mait.ac.in|language=en-gb|access-date=2018-05-29}}</ref>  It has a multi-storey boy's hostel, a multi-storey library, amphitheatre, main auditorium, mini auditorium, five canteens, a gym, a boys common room, indoor badminton courts, tennis, volleyball and basketball courts and a main playground.\n\n== Cultural and non-academic activities ==\nTechSurge & Mridang are the annual techno-cultural festivals of MAIT. TechSurge conjures up a vivid spectrum of science and technology.\n\nApart from the annual festivals, the college has various societies like DOTC, Codematrix, IOSD, ACM, IEEE:MAIT, TechTronix and TEAM JATAYU to help the students develop the required skills in their fields. AAYAAM is the theatre society, LITERARY UMBRELLA is the literary society and AFFINITY is the music society of the college.\n\n== Rankings ==\nMAIT has been ranked as the 10th best private engineering institute in India by the [[Dataquest]] T-School Survey.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.dqindia.com/meet-indias-top-100-private-t-schools-for-2016/|title=Meet India's Top 100 Private T-Schools for 2016DATAQUEST|website=www.dqindia.com|language=en-US|access-date=2018-06-19}}</ref> MAIT was ranked 98 among engineering colleges in India by ''[[Outlook India]]'' in 2015.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.outlookindia.com/magazine|title=outlookindia.com - more than just the news magazine from India|website=https://www.outlookindia.com/|access-date=2018-06-19}}</ref>\n\n==Notable alumni==\n* Dr. Puneet Gupta, Assistant Professor at [[IIT Indore]]<ref>{{cite web|url=http://iiti.ac.in/people/~puneet/ |title=Puneet Gupta }}</ref>\n*\n\n==External links==\n* {{official|http://www.mait.ac.in/}}\n\n==References==\n{{Commons category|Maharaja Agrasen Institute of Technology, New Delhi}}\n{{Reflist}}\n\n{{Guru Gobind Singh Indraprastha University}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Maharaja Agrasen Institute Of Technology, New Delhi}}\n[[Category:Engineering colleges in Delhi]]\n[[Category:Colleges of the Guru Gobind Singh Indraprastha University]]\n[[Category:Memorials to Agrasen]]\n", "text_old": "{{Use dmy dates|date=October 2018}}\n{{Use Indian English|date=October 2018}}\n{{Infobox university\n| name = Maharaja Agrasen Institute of Technology\n| image_name = Maharaja Agrasen Institute of Technology logo.PNG\n| caption = \n| established = 1999\n| type = [[Private school|Private]]\n| motto = Udyamena hi sidhyanti karyani na manorathaih ([[Sanskrit]])\n| mottoeng = Work gets accomplished by effort, not merely by wishing\n| director = Nand Kishore Garg <ref>https://www.mait.ac.in/index.php/institute/director-general-message</ref>\n| head_label = Neelam Sharma\t\n| city = [[New Delhi]]\n| country = [[India]]\n| faculty = \n| students = \n| coordinates = {{coord|28.722366|77.065980|region:IN-DL_type:edu|display=inline,title}}\n| campus = [[urban area|Urban]]\n| free_label = Nickname\n| free = MAIT\n| affiliations = [[Guru Gobind Singh Indraprastha University]]\n| colours = Red {{color box|#cc0000}}\n| website = {{url|http://www.mait.ac.in/}}\n}}\n\n'''Maharaja Agrasen Institute of Technology''' ('''MAIT''') is a private engineering college, located in [[Rohini, Delhi]], [[India]].  Established in 1999, the institute is approved by [[AICTE]] and affiliated to [[Guru Gobind Singh Indraprastha University]].<ref name=\":0\"/>\n\n== Departments ==\n\n; Sciences \n\n* Applied Sciences\n\n; Management \n\n* MBA\n\n== Admission ==\nAdmission to all courses is through common counseling of [[Guru Gobind Singh Indraprastha University]].\n\n==Campus==\n[[File:MAIT Administrative Block.JPG|thumb|Administrative Block]]\n[[File:MAIT Library.JPG|thumb|MAIT Library|alt=|180x180px]]MAIT\u2019s campus is composed of 10 blocks with a learning resource centre.<ref name=\":0\">{{Cite web|url=http://mait.ac.in/|title=Welcome to MAIT|website=mait.ac.in|language=en-gb|access-date=2018-05-29}}</ref>  It has a multi-storey boy's hostel, a multi-storey library, amphitheatre, main auditorium, mini auditorium, five canteens, a gym, a boys common room, indoor badminton courts, tennis, volleyball and basketball courts and a main playground.\n\n== Cultural and non-academic activities ==\nTechSurge & Mridang are the annual techno-cultural festivals of MAIT. TechSurge conjures up a vivid spectrum of science and technology.\n\nApart from the annual festivals, the college has various societies like DOTC, Codematrix, IOSD, ACM, IEEE:MAIT, TechTronix and TEAM JATAYU to help the students develop the required skills in their fields. AAYAAM is the theatre society, LITERARY UMBRELLA is the literary society and AFFINITY is the music society of the college.\n\n== Rankings ==\nMAIT has been ranked as the 10th best private engineering institute in India by the [[Dataquest]] T-School Survey.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.dqindia.com/meet-indias-top-100-private-t-schools-for-2016/|title=Meet India's Top 100 Private T-Schools for 2016DATAQUEST|website=www.dqindia.com|language=en-US|access-date=2018-06-19}}</ref> MAIT was ranked 98 among engineering colleges in India by ''[[Outlook India]]'' in 2015.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.outlookindia.com/magazine|title=outlookindia.com - more than just the news magazine from India|website=https://www.outlookindia.com/|access-date=2018-06-19}}</ref>\n\n==Notable alumni==\n* Dr. Puneet Gupta, Assistant Professor at [[IIT Indore]]<ref>{{cite web|url=http://iiti.ac.in/people/~puneet/ |title=Puneet Gupta }}</ref>\n*Harsh Poddar, Founder and CEO at HVN Powercare\n\n==External links==\n* {{official|http://www.mait.ac.in/}}\n\n==References==\n{{Commons category|Maharaja Agrasen Institute of Technology, New Delhi}}\n{{Reflist}}\n\n{{Guru Gobind Singh Indraprastha University}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Maharaja Agrasen Institute Of Technology, New Delhi}}\n[[Category:Engineering colleges in Delhi]]\n[[Category:Colleges of the Guru Gobind Singh Indraprastha University]]\n[[Category:Memorials to Agrasen]]\n", "name_user": "JRDkg", "label": "safe", "comment": "Unsourced..", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Maharaja_Agrasen_Institute_of_Technology"}
